<topic id='element_date_of_primary_cancer_diagnosis__clinically_agreed_.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Data Element: DATE OF PRIMARY CANCER DIAGNOSIS (CLINICALLY AGREED) - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_date_of_primary_cancer_diagnosis__clinically_agreed_">DATE OF PRIMARY CANCER DIAGNOSIS (CLINICALLY AGREED)</xref>
 is the same as data element 
              <xref outputclass="element" keyref="element_diagnosis_date">DIAGNOSIS DATE</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="element"
               keyref="element_date_of_primary_cancer_diagnosis__clinically_agreed_">DATE OF PRIMARY CANCER DIAGNOSIS (CLINICALLY AGREED)</xref>
 is either the date:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
the 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_primary_cancer">Primary Cancer</xref>
 was confirmed or                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
the 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_primary_cancer">Primary Cancer</xref>
 diagnosis was agreed                    </p>
            </div>
            <ul>
               <li>
                  <div>
                     <p>
this will normally be the date of the authorised 
                                            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                              keyref="business_definition_pathology_laboratory_service_report">Pathology Laboratory Service Report</xref>
 which confirms the 
                                            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                              keyref="business_definition_primary_cancer">Primary Cancer</xref>
 or                            </p>
                  </div>
               </li>
               <li>
                  <div>
                     <p>
if this date is not available, 
                                            <xref outputclass="element"
                              keyref="element_date_of_primary_cancer_diagnosis__clinically_agreed_">DATE OF PRIMARY CANCER DIAGNOSIS (CLINICALLY AGREED)</xref>
 will be the date of the 
                                            <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                              keyref="business_definition_multidisciplinary_team_meeting">Multidisciplinary Team Meeting</xref>.                            </p>
                  </div>
               </li>
            </ul>
         </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
</body>
